##Deep Breath in an epidemic. | Hope he can be a useful person to society

Micro Signal Xiezuozheyunshegong

FUNCTION INTRODUCTION: Volunteer Information Management, social worker information management, public welfare information release, social work professional exchange

This article is one of the case interviews conducted by the collaborators in the "Peasant Workers' anti-epidemic Rescue Action" , aiming at quickly identifying the vulnerable groups and their needs in the epidemic situation, and providing reference for the epidemic prevention, control and rescue work, we put it together and share it with you.

Deep breathing in case of an outbreak
A case study of migrant workers families in distress (11)

I hope he can be of use to society

Narrator: Ah Chen (not her real name) / Xin Yi Ji, Guangdong Province
Place of employment: Zhuhai

Editor's Note: a Zhen, 76, is from Guangdong Province. Since 1990, with his wife to live in Zhuhai, the son because of usury can not repay, ran away from home, has not returned, daughter-in-law also therefore remarry. The two men make a living as farmers, taking care of their high school grandsons and occasionally supporting their daughters to make ends meet.

A family like ours, we don't know where to start

I came to Zhuhai for 31 years, when I first came to Zhuhai, growing sugar cane, after a variety of reasons did not grow sugar cane, to grow vegetables for a living, occasionally go out to sell vegetables. During the current epidemic, some of the vegetables picked are eaten by family members, and the rest are sold at the market. They sell 10 Jin, 8 Jin at a time, and they go to the market 3-5 times a week. Nowadays, very few people in the market go home after 7:00 in the evening. They can earn tens of yuan each time, he rarely goes out the rest of the time. A few days ago in the vegetable plot of the Dwarf was pulled, do not know who did, the night nobody guard, now people have become very powerful, before no one will steal, now did not expect so much rampant.

Listen to the village brigade said that in the future to re-planning the land, we need to rent land to grow vegetables. After two years of almost no income, now I can only grow my own food... the daily living expenses are dependent on the low-income allowance of a few hundred yuan, as well as the co-worker's family to build a library monthly subsidy. The son left, borrowed usury can not repay, can not contact again, the daughter-in-law remarried, only the grandson and we live alone. And my daughter's support, I wouldn't know what to do. Occasionally their sick to go to the doctor with their daughter, the second daughter is not easy to help others sell breakfast, a month of about 1000 yuan, her husband broke a leg without work, the family also rely on her own.

Co-author social worker visits ah Chen's family (photo taken in May 2016)

In October 2019, my feet and waist were so inflamed that my daughter took me to get medicine, and now I'm almost out of medicine and have no money to go back to the doctor. My husband's feet have been hurting lately, and with the flu, he hasn't been to work, and he doesn't get paid, and the doctor says he can't do any heavy work. I had to go around and see if there was any yams I could pick and rub on him. Now I am more and more worried that I am getting older, the movement is not too convenient, the body can not plant the land. Migrant workers delayed returning to work, went out to sell vegetables no one to buy, also can not earn money. My daughter didn't come to visit us after years, they couldn't go to work either, only my third daughter started working, mostly cleaning, but she didn't earn enough to support her family..

And I don't know how to say what support I need, and now families like ours, we don't know where to start.
I hope that in the future he can go to college and become a useful person to the society

My grandson was brought up by me and his grandfather.

The grandson is thinner, eat less at home, feel the home food is not good enough to eat, school food choice more. He also lived frugally and ate the cheapest meals at school. He also recently had a cold and a runny nose. He didn't see a doctor. He just took some medicine by himself.

Sun Tzu will be a senior next semester, he is also very helpless, want to go to school can not go. Their school began online classes on February 17, I use the Keypad, grandson has a very old smartphone can barely use, connected to the neighbor's network, we do not have Internet at home. According to Sun Tzu, the new head teacher who teaches mathematics in the school is from Hubei Province, because she could not come to teach them after the epidemic was estimated.

Nearby children come to the community self-help library run by ah Chen's grandson to read

I don't know how Sun Tzu Studies, he doesn't say, sometimes I don't understand. But to see that he can take the initiative to learn, consciously complete the homework, hope that he can be admitted to university in the future, to become a useful person to society. But I am more worried about the need to review the college entrance examination, the epidemic delayed the start of school will not delay Sun Tzu's studies. Start School need to pay 800 yuan tuition fees, food costs 500 yuan a month, after also need to pay. None of this is in place yet.
There's no use in being afraid. Just do what you have to do

I didn't know about it until my grandson came home from vacation and told me about the new pneumonia. A long time ago there was a store of masks, there is no disinfectant in the house, and no purchase. Didn't pay much attention at first, didn't go out much, didn't wear a mask. A few days ago the village committee gave disposable medical masks, and your collaborators sent several N95 can be reused. Now when I use a piece of paper in the mask, go out for a while to use. I went out to sell vegetables, I noticed two little girls outside the market, put their hand-sanitizer masks on their faces and hands, and I saw others doing the same thing, and I didn't know to put them in an air-conditioned place until you reminded me. I'll keep an eye on my own back.

At present, the new pneumonia is not very afraid, afraid is also of no use, how should be how, all faith fate, I do not understand. But it's just not convenient to go out right now, and it's not convenient to get some money. The plan was to let the grandson go out to take out the low guarantee money, for daily expenses, food, do not take out to worry about later to use, basic living expenses, grandson also have to pay tuition. The bank did not know when to open, went several times, all in vain, and now also can not get the money.

Social Worker's notes


Talk can feel strong grandma, because of age and disease and gradually become powerless, always believe in the master of fate, step by step. The sudden outbreak of the epidemic is let her worry about her wife's body, daughter's family life, grandson's study... but grandma always with hope and joy, she hope grandson can study hard, become a useful person in society. This hope accompanied her, hard, positive, upward life.

Service advice
Now:
Coordination of relief resources and provision of emergency livelihood assistance;
2. To provide personalized epidemic prevention knowledge guidance and training for family members, link the necessary protective supplies to ensure the livelihood security of family members;
3. During the outbreak, children were invited to participate in online study groups to enhance the ability of self-conscious learning and communication with others, to relieve the psychological pressure of the elderly at home.

LONG-TERM:
1. Invite your child to continue to participate in the collaborative community service to enhance leadership, resilience and other aspects of capacity;
2. Provide college entrance examination guidance, including homework review, test skills, test volunteers, etc. 
3. Link Medical Volunteers and relief resources to provide family members with basic support services such as health, medical care and medical check-up.
